2D ARRAY

2D array consists of rows and columns, the very first square bracket indicates rows and square bracket indicates columns.
while declaring the array, we have to declare number of rows and columns, numbers are optional. Each row will act as an individual array.

for a 2*3 array

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);
        int[][] arr = new int[2][3];
        
        for(int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < arr[i].length; j++) {
                arr[i][j] = in.nextInt(); 
            }
        }

        for(int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < arr[i].length; j++) {
                System.out.print(arr[i][j] + " ");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}

input:
2 3 4
7 6 12
output:
2 3 4
7 6 12





















